China's 14th Five-Year Plan (2021-2025) is considered a blueprint for China's economic and social development over the coming five years. Carrie Lam, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), once said: "Every word in it carries enormous weight." She also believes it will bring Hong Kong vitality and golden opportunities. So why does Carrie Lam have such high expectations for this plan? And how important is it to Hong Kong? Let's check it out!